# Attendance Intelligence Platform — Comprehensive Project Analysis

---

## 1. What Is This Project?

The **Attendance Intelligence Platform** is an enterprise-grade, AI-powered workforce management system. It uses **smart cameras (edge devices)** with face recognition to automatically track employee attendance, monitor real-time physical presence inside buildings, and surface intelligent HR analytics — all secured behind **Keycloak** authentication, persisted in **PostgreSQL**, and streamed via **Kafka**.

---

## 2. High-Level Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph "Edge Layer"
        CAM["Smart Cameras<br/>(Face Recognition)"]
    end

    subgraph "Streaming Layer"
        KAFKA["Apache Kafka<br/>Event Bus"]
    end

    subgraph "Backend Layer"
        API["Express.js API Server"]
        RULES["Rules Engine<br/>(BaseRule subclasses)"]
        MODELS["AI ModelManager<br/>(OpenVINO .xml/.bin)"]
        WS["WebSocket / SSE<br/>Realtime Push"]
    end

    subgraph "Data Layer"
        PG["PostgreSQL<br/>(9 migrations)"]
        KC["Keycloak<br/>(Auth + RBAC)"]
    end

    subgraph "Frontend Layer"
        UI["React + Vite + Tailwind<br/>(96 components)"]
    end

    CAM -->|AttendanceEvent| KAFKA
    KAFKA --> API
    API --> RULES
    API --> MODELS
    API --> PG
    API --> KC
    API --> WS
    WS --> UI
    UI -->|REST calls| API
```

---

## 3. The Application Blueprint (Single Source of Truth)

The `application-blueprint/` folder is a **technology-agnostic logical blueprint** containing 13 JSON definition files. It is designed so the entire application can theoretically be regenerated from scratch in any stack.

| Blueprint File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| [application.json](file:///c:/Yash/FRS/application-blueprint/blueprint/application.json) | Top-level app metadata |
| [modules.json](file:///c:/Yash/FRS/application-blueprint/blueprint/modules.json) | 9 functional modules (Auth, Device Mgmt, HR, etc.) |
| [models.json](file:///c:/Yash/FRS/application-blueprint/blueprint/models.json) | 10 data entities (Employee, Device, Building, Floor, Area, etc.) |
| [apis.json](file:///c:/Yash/FRS/application-blueprint/blueprint/apis.json) | 4 API groups with 17 total endpoints |
| [events.json](file:///c:/Yash/FRS/application-blueprint/blueprint/events.json) | 4 event types (AttendanceEvent, DeviceStatus, PresenceSession, Alert) |
| [realtime.json](file:///c:/Yash/FRS/application-blueprint/blueprint/realtime.json) | 4 real-time streams (WebSocket + SSE) |
| [roles.json](file:///c:/Yash/FRS/application-blueprint/blueprint/roles.json) | 4 RBAC roles with granular permissions |
| [ui-pages.json](file:///c:/Yash/FRS/application-blueprint/blueprint/ui-pages.json) | 6 UI pages mapped to routes and components |
| [components.json](file:///c:/Yash/FRS/application-blueprint/blueprint/components.json) | 8 reusable dashboard widgets |
| [facility.json](file:///c:/Yash/FRS/application-blueprint/blueprint/facility.json) | Sample facility hierarchy (Building → Floor → Area → Camera) |
| [relationships.json](file:///c:/Yash/FRS/application-blueprint/blueprint/relationships.json) | 10 entity relationships (many-to-one, one-to-one) |
| [business-rules.json](file:///c:/Yash/FRS/application-blueprint/blueprint/business-rules.json) | 5 core business rules (grace periods, confidence thresholds, etc.) |
| [structure.json](file:///c:/Yash/FRS/application-blueprint/blueprint/structure.json) | Folder layout reference |

---

## 4. RBAC & Permissions (Keycloak)

Four roles, each with scoped permissions:

| Role | Permissions | UI Access |
|---|---|---|
| **Super Admin** | `tenant:create/update/delete`, `admin:create/view`, `system:config` | Everything |
| **Admin** | `user:*`, `device:*`, `facility:manage`, `audit:read`, `report:generate` | Admin Dashboard, Operations Console, Facility Console |
| **HR Manager** | `employee:*`, `attendance:read/modify`, `shift:manage`, `insights:view` | HR Dashboard, Presence Monitor, Employee Profiles |
| **Employee** | `profile:read/update`, `attendance:own_read`, `leave:request` | Self-service portal |

The backend enforces this via middleware:
- [keycloakJwtMiddleware.js](file:///c:/Yash/FRS/backend/src/middleware/keycloakJwtMiddleware.js) — Validates Keycloak JWT tokens
- [keycloakVerifier.js](file:///c:/Yash/FRS/backend/src/middleware/keycloakVerifier.js) — JWKS-based signature verification
- [authz.js](file:///c:/Yash/FRS/backend/src/middleware/authz.js) — Permission-level authorization checks
- [scopeExtractor.js](file:///c:/Yash/FRS/backend/src/middleware/scopeExtractor.js) — Multi-tenant scope extraction (tenant → customer → site → unit)

---

## 5. API Contract (17 Endpoints)

| Group | Base URL | Endpoints |
|---|---|---|
| **Employee APIs** | `/api/employees` | `GET /` list, `GET /:id`, `POST /` create, `PUT /:id` update, `DELETE /:id` deactivate |
| **Device APIs** | `/api/devices` | `GET /` list, `GET /:id` status, `POST /` register, `PUT /:id` update, `DELETE /:id` remove, `POST /:id/command` ping/reboot |
| **Attendance APIs** | `/api/attendance` | `GET /` historical logs, `POST /events` webhook ingestion, `GET /summary` aggregated stats |
| **Presence APIs** | `/api/presence` | `GET /` zone occupancy, `GET /sessions` dwell times, `GET /live` stream config |

Additional backend routes not in the blueprint: `authRoutes`, `dashboardRoutes`, `faceRoutes`, `healthRoutes`, `liveRoutes`, `meRoutes`, `reportRoutes`, `searchRoutes`.

