## 7. Event System & Real-Time Streams

### 4 Event Types

| Event | Source | Trigger |
|---|---|---|
| **AttendanceEvent** | Device | Camera validates a face at entry/exit |
| **DeviceStatusChanged** | System | Heartbeat missed or restored |
| **PresenceSessionStarted** | System | Employee enters a tracked zone |
| **AlertTriggered** | System | Rule violation or system error |

### 4 Real-Time Channels

| Channel | Protocol | Subscribers |
|---|---|---|
| Device Health Stream | **WebSocket** | Device Management, Admin Panel |
| Live Attendance Feed | **WebSocket** | Attendance, HR Panel |
| System Alerts Channel | **SSE** | Admin Panel, HR Panel |
| Zone Occupancy Stream | **WebSocket** | Presence Monitoring, Facility Intelligence |

### Kafka Subsystem (`backend/src/core/kafka/`)

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `KafkaConfig.js` | Broker connection, topic definitions |
| `KafkaProducer.js` | Publishes events to Kafka topics |
| `KafkaConsumer.js` | Subscribes to and processes Kafka messages |
| `KafkaEventService.js` | Orchestrates event routing between Kafka and the rules engine |

Kafka topics (from `env.js`): `raw-frames`, `detections`, `events`, `alerts`, `smart-search`, `smart-search-results`, `system-metrics`, `snapshots`.

---

## 8. Business Rules

| Rule | Description | Parameter |
|---|---|---|
| **Check-in Grace Period** | Employees within X min of shift start = ON TIME | `graceMinutes: 15` |
| **Face Match Confidence** | Events below Y confidence → manual review | `minConfidenceScore: 0.85` |
| **Auto-Checkout Timeout** | No EXIT event by shift end + 4hrs → auto-generate EXIT | `autoCheckoutDelayHours: 4` |
| **Consecutive Absence Alert** | N days absent without leave → HR alert | `consecutiveDaysTrigger: 3` |
| **Device Offline Heartbeat** | Missed ping for M seconds → mark Offline | `missedHeartbeatSeconds: 60` |

---

## 9. AI Models & Rules Engine

### AI Models (`backend/models/`)

| Folder | Model Files | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `Face/` | `face.xml`, `face.bin`, `face.mapping`, `face.yaml` | Face detection |
| `Fv/` | `fv.xml`, `fv.bin`, `fv.mapping` | Person/Vehicle detection |
| `Landmarks/` | `landmarks.xml`, `landmarks.bin` | Facial landmarks |

Managed by `ModelManager.js` which loads, warms up, and exposes these models for inference.

### Rules Engine (`backend/src/core/rules/`)

| Rule File | Example Rules |
|---|---|
| `SecurityRules.js` | BackdoorEntryViolation, CameraTemper, CameraAngleChange |
| `SafetyRules.js` | HelmetWeapon, FallDown |
| `DemographicsRules.js` | AgeGenderClassify, GenderDemographics |
| `TrafficAndTransitRules.js` | TrainArrivalDeparture, TrainIntrusion, VehicleZoneIntrusion |
| `OccupancyAndPresenceRules.js` | OverCrowding, SmartOccupancy, Loitering |
| `RetailAndBankingRules.js` | ATMSafeOrHoodOpen, VaultPersonDwellTime |
| `DeviceManagementRules.js` | PmsRuleEnableOnPi, Pms |
| `MiscellaneousRules.js` | AnimalCounting, Cleanliness, InsectPresence, PetWithoutPerson |

All rules extend `BaseRule.js` and implement an `evaluate()` method.

