## 10. Backend Architecture (Express.js)

```
backend/src/
├── config/          # env.js, loaders.js (config management)
├── controllers/     # 6 controllers (Attendance, Dashboard, Employee, Face, Report, Search)
├── core/
│   ├── db/          # SQLite face DB
│   ├── infra/       # Infrastructure utilities
│   ├── kafka/       # 4 Kafka files (Config, Consumer, Producer, EventService)
│   ├── managers/    # ModelManager (AI model lifecycle)
│   ├── rules/       # 10 rule files (BaseRule + 8 category files + index)
│   ├── services/    # 6 core services (Inference, EventPush, Snapshot, Validation, etc.)
│   ├── util/        # 7 utility files
│   └── workers/     # Background workers
├── db/
│   ├── migrations/  # 9 SQL migration files
│   └── pool.js      # PostgreSQL connection pool
├── middleware/       # 9 middleware files (auth, authz, Keycloak, rate-limit, scope, upload)
├── repositories/    # 5 data access files (auth, device, event, live, scopeSql)
├── routes/          # 11 route files
├── services/
│   ├── business/    # 6 business services (Attendance, Dashboard, Employee, Live, Report, Search)
│   ├── authService.js
│   ├── tokenService.js
│   ├── identityMappingService.js
│   └── provisionUser.js
├── validators/      # Input validation (Joi/Zod)
├── websocket/       # WebSocket handlers for realtime push
└── server.js        # Express app entry point
```

---

## 11. Frontend Architecture (React + Vite + Tailwind)

```
src/
├── app/
│   ├── App.tsx           # Root component
│   ├── components/       # 96 UI components
│   ├── config/           # Frontend configuration
│   ├── contexts/         # React contexts (Auth, Theme)
│   ├── data/             # Mock data providers
│   ├── engine/           # Client-side processing engine
│   ├── hooks/            # Custom React hooks
│   ├── services/         # 10 API service modules
│   ├── types/            # TypeScript type definitions
│   └── utils/            # Utility functions
├── styles/               # Global CSS
└── theme/                # Theme configuration
```

The frontend uses `VITE_AUTH_MODE` (mock vs api) to switch between development mock data and the live backend.

