## 12. Infrastructure & Deployment

### Docker Compose Files

| File | Services |
|---|---|
| `docker-compose.yml` | Keycloak standalone (dev) |
| `docker-compose.keycloak.yml` | Full stack: Keycloak + Keycloak-DB (Postgres) + App Postgres + Backend |

### Key Environment Variables (from `.env.example`)
- **Auth**: `AUTH_MODE`, `KEYCLOAK_URL`, `KEYCLOAK_REALM`, `KEYCLOAK_ISSUER`, `KEYCLOAK_JWKS_URI`
- **Database**: `DB_HOST`, `DB_PORT`, `DB_NAME`, `DB_USER`, `DB_PASSWORD`
- **Kafka**: `KAFKA_BROKERS`, `KAFKA_CLIENT_ID`, `KAFKA_GROUP_ID`, plus 8 topic configs
- **AI**: `MODEL_PATH`, `INFERENCE_THREADS`, `MAX_HEAP_MEMORY_PERCENT`
- **Frontend**: `VITE_AUTH_MODE`, `VITE_API_BASE_URL`

---

## 13. End-to-End Data Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Cam as Smart Camera
    participant Kafka as Kafka Bus
    participant API as Express Backend
    participant Rules as Rules Engine
    participant PG as PostgreSQL
    participant WS as WebSocket
    participant UI as React Frontend
    participant KC as Keycloak

    Cam->>Kafka: Publish AttendanceEvent (face detected)
    Kafka->>API: Consume event from topic
    API->>Rules: Evaluate (confidence check, security rules)
    Rules-->>API: Event validated
    API->>PG: INSERT attendance_event + UPDATE presence_session
    API->>WS: Push real-time update
    UI->>KC: Verify JWT token
    KC-->>UI: Token valid (role: hr)
    WS->>UI: attendance.updated event
    UI->>UI: Dashboard updates live count
```

---

